Provides pretty-printing capabilities for Facet types.

Example:

```rust,no_run
use facet::Facet;
use facet_pretty::FacetPretty;

#[derive(Debug, Facet)]
struct Person {
    name: String,
    age: u32,
}

fn main() {
    let person = Person {
        name: "Alice".to_string(),
        age: 30,
    };
    println!("Default pretty-printing:");
    println!("{}", person.pretty());
}
```

Produces the output:

```rust,no_run
Person {
  name: "Alice",
  age: 30,
}
```